  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hurricane Tomas - St Lucia Recovery</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hurricane Tomas hit St Lucia and surrounding Caribbean nations on 29 October 2010 causing loss of lives, widespread damage to residential properties, business properties, infrastructure and agricultural land. Funding under this initiative provides financial support for recovery and rehabilitation in St Lucia, specifically: for an early warning system and hydrological monitoring for water management and disaster risk reduction; and for forest rehabilitation and restoration. The total value of this initiative is $0.9 million over 2 years, starting 2010-11.</narrative>
  </description>
